# Structure

## Directories (baseline)
- `/src`
  - `/components` — pure UI, small reusable units
  - `/features` — domain-specific composite UI
  - `/stores` — Zustand slices
  - `/lib` — utilities, validators, formatters
  - `/lib/hooks` — custom React hooks
  - `/api` — domain API functions + mocks
  - `/styles` — globals, variables, mixins
  - `/types` — shared TypeScript types
  - `/constants` — enums, constants
  - `/config` — environment configs, feature flags
  - `/assets` — images, icons, fonts
  - `/pages` — routing entry (framework-specific)

## Conventions
- One component per file; colocate SCSS and tests with the component.
- Use index barrels only when they improve DX and do not cause circular deps.
- Import paths use the `@/` alias from project root (configured via `tsconfig` `paths`).
- Place large integration/E2E tests under `/tests` or `/e2e` (not next to components).

## File Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Stores: `*Store.ts`
- Hooks: `use*.ts`
- Tests: `*.test.ts(x)` colocated or in `__tests__/`
- Mocks: `*.mock.ts`
